ZH: 我喜欢用胶片相机拍照。
EN: I like taking photos with a film camera.

ZH: 这是我最喜欢的一卷胶片。
EN: This is my favorite roll of film.

ZH: 我想试试黑白胶片的效果。
EN: I want to try the effect of black and white film.

ZH: 胶片照片在阳光下更有意境。
EN: Film photos have more artistic feeling in the sunlight.

ZH: 他在胶片中捕捉到了美丽的风景。
EN: He captured beautiful landscapes on film.

ZH: 我们使用胶片记录了我们的旅行记忆。
EN: We used film to capture our travel memories.

ZH: 胶片不如数码照片方便存储。
EN: Film is not as convenient for storage as digital photos.

ZH: 我收藏了很多复古的胶片相机。
EN: I have collected many vintage film cameras.

ZH: 胶片摄影是一门艺术。
EN: Film photography is an art.

ZH: 他喜欢用老式的胶片拍摄人像。
EN: He likes to shoot portraits with old film.

ZH: 我发现自己越来越喜欢胶片拍摄。
EN: I find myself more and more drawn to film photography.

ZH: 胶片照片有一种独特的质感。
EN: Film photos have a unique quality.

ZH: 我们家庭相簿里装满了胶片照片。
EN: Our family album is filled with film photos.

ZH: 这次摄影展展出了很多胶片作品。
EN: This photography exhibition showcases many film works.

ZH: 胶片摄影需要更专业的技能和经验。
EN: Film photography requires more professional skills and experience.

ZH: 我把这些胶片邮寄到澳大利亚去冲洗。
EN: I sent these films to Australia for developing.

ZH: 胶片拍摄给我带来了更大的满足感。
EN: Film photography brings me greater satisfaction.

ZH: 胶片拍摄不会受到数码设备的限制。
EN: Film photography is not limited by digital devices.

ZH: 胶片冲洗的费用比数码打印贵。
EN: Developing film is more expensive than digital printing.
